1. at CamLaserCalibraTool/CMakeLists.txt:37 (find_package):
  By not providing "FindCeres.cmake" in CMAKE_MODULE_PATH this project has
  asked CMake to find a package configuration file provided by "Ceres", but
  CMake did not find one.

   P: need to install ceres 
   S: # install dependencies
        # CMake
        sudo apt-get install cmake
        # google-glog + gflags
        sudo apt-get install libgoogle-glog-dev libgflags-dev
        # BLAS & LAPACK
        sudo apt-get install libatlas-base-dev
        # Eigen3
        sudo apt-get install libeigen3-dev
        # SuiteSparse and CXSparse (optional)
        sudo apt-get install libsuitesparse-dev
        
        # add the following PPA:
        sudo add-apt-repository ppa:bzindovic/suitesparse-bugfix-1319687



        # install ceres
        git clone https://ceres-solver.googlesource.com/ceres-solver
        cd ceres-solver
        mkdir ceres-bin
        cd ceres-bin
        cmake ..
        make
        make test
        sudo make install


2. E: The repository 'http://ppa.launchpad.net/bzindovic/suitesparse-bugfix-1319687/ubuntu bionic Release' does not have a Release file.
   R: ppa version is too old 
   S: # clean the previous ppa
      sudo add-apt-repository -r ppa:bzindovic/suitesparse-bugfix-1319687
      sudo apt update
      # go to https://github.com/jluttine/suitesparse 
      git clone https://github.com/jluttine/suitesparse.git
      cd suitesparse
      make
      make library


